<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-11T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-11T12:00:00-05:00" n="1170" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1170">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                                Kashmir/3–1149: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-11T12:00:00-05:00">March
                                        11, 1949—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>811. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 765 Mar 2.<note n="1" xml:id="d1170fn1">Not printed.</note>
                                <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> repeal embargo now being
                                prepared Pres’s consideration having been cleared Secys State and
                                Defense. Dept anticipates early favorable action Pres. Due
                                limitations availability arms this country, however, repeal will
                                have little effect our supply to <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>
                                and <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss>.</p>
                            <p>Dept currently being pressed for arms procurement assistance and
                                supply from Govt sources by <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>,
                                    <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> and Afghanistan. In order
                                better appraise their needs Dept would appreciate such info as Emb
                                can obtain informally re UK arms deliveries these countries.</p>
                            <p>Dept also interested knowing whether <gloss target="#t_CRO1">CRO</gloss> decision to no longer inform each Dominion of UK
                                arms deliveries to other signifies any basic change UK policy re
                                supply arms to <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss>.</p>
                            <p>Rptd to New Delhi, Karachi, Kabul as <gloss target="#t_agram1">agam</gloss>.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>